# Bike Sales Analysis Project

This repository contains an end-to-end analysis of bike sales data using Power BI. The project aims to provide insights into bike sales trends, product performance, and customer segmentation.

## Table of Contents

- [Introduction](#introduction)
- [Data Source](#data-source)
- [Analysis Overview](#analysis-overview)
- [Power BI Report](#power-bi-report)
- [How to Use](#how-to-use)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- license


## Introduction

In today's competitive market, understanding sales trends and customer behavior is crucial for business success. This project utilizes bike sales data to perform a comprehensive analysis and derive actionable insights for business stakeholders.

## Data Source

The dataset used for this analysis consists of historical bike sales data. The dataset includes information such as sales transactions, product details, customer demographics, etc. The data has been preprocessed and cleaned for analysis.

## Analysis Overview

The analysis covers the following key areas:

- Sales trends over time (2019, 2020, 2021)
- Product performance analysis
- Customer segmentation
- Profitability analysis
- Sales forecasting

## Power BI Report

The Power BI report provides interactive visualizations and dashboards to explore the bike sales data. The report includes:
- Various charts and graphs to visualize sales trends, product performance, etc.
- Interactive slicers and filters for data exploration
- Calculated measures and KPIs for performance evaluation

![Power BI Dashboard](link-to-power-bi-dashboard)

## How to Use

To view the Power BI report:
1. Clone this repository to your local machine.
2. Open the `Bike_Sales_Analysis.pbix` file using Power BI Desktop.
3. Explore the interactive visualizations and dashboards.

